		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 highlander-comment" id="li-comment-1291">
		<div id="comment-1291">
			<cite class="fn">john</cite>			<a href="http://bloodyshovel.wordpress.com/2012/11/22/the-brain-drain-trap/#comment-1291">November 27, 2012 at 21:13</a>
						<div class="comment-body"><p>Another thing that I don&#8217;t agree is somehow the country &#8220;gives&#8221; money to the masses to bring up their living standard. What actually happens in a country like China is that, as the country climbs the value added chain, there is more money to spread around so people are paid more. Also as the population decreases and more industries come up, the cost of hiring workers goes up due to supply and demand, the companies are now forced to invest more money to make each employee more productive. This is a virtuous cycle which a declining working age population will contribute to. These are very huge macro economic forces which will only be moved by policy and macro economic shifts and not by simply giving more to the masses.</p>
</div>

